.homepage-header
.container
    .row{ :style => "margin-top: -300px"}
        .col-xs-12.col-md-4
            .homepage-header-content
                .text-large.text-primary
                    = t("views.alt.whats_a_fab_lab", default: "What is a Fablab?")
                .text-medium
                    = t("views.alt.fab_labs_description", default: "A Fab Lab, or digital fabrication laboratory, is a place to play, to to create, to learn, to mentor, to invent: a place for learning and innovation. <br/> Fab Labs provide access to the environment, the skills, the materials and the advanced technology to allow anyone anywhere to make (almost) anything.<br><br><a href='http://www.fabfoundation.org'>Learn more</a>", fab_foundation: (link_to "Fab Foundation", "http://www.fabfoundation.org") ).html_safe
        .col-xs-12.col-md-4
            .homepage-header-content
                .text-large.text-primary
                    = t("views.alt.how_to_start", default: "How to start a Fablab?")
                .text-medium
                    = t("views.alt.how_to_start_description", default: "<p>You are on the front wave of a new, international movement in personal fabrication. The cheapest and fastest method to get a fab lab is to buy  and assemble it yourself. This approach does require that you have some good expertise on hand to help you set up,  install, debug and train.<br><br><a href='https://fabfoundation.org/getting-started/#fab-lab-questions'>Learn More</a></p>", fab_foundation: (link_to "Fab Foundation", "http://www.fabfoundation.org") ).html_safe
        .col-xs-12.col-md-4
            .homepage-header-content
                .text-large.text-primary
                    = t("views.home.find_a_fablab", default: "Find a Fablab")
                .text-medium
                    = t("views.alt.find_a_fablab_description", default: "<p>The Fab Lab Network is an open creative community of fabricators, artists, scientists, engineers, educators, students, amateurs and professionals located in more than 100 countries and 1,750 Fab Labs across the globe.</p><br><a href='/labs/map'>Browse the labs map</a>" ).html_safe
    .row.homepage-boxes
        .col-xs-12.col-md-6
            .homepage-box
                =image_tag ("home/lab-illustration.png"), :class => "homepage-box-image"
                .text-small
                    = t("views.alt.lab_card.subtitle", default: "Getting started")
                .text-large
                    = t("views.alt.lab_card.title", default: "Fablabs.io")
                .text-medium
                    = t("views.alt.lab_card.description", default: "Welcome to Fablabs.io and the Fablab Network, an open, creative community of fabricators, artists, scientists, engineers, educators, students, amateurs, professionals, ages 5 to 75+, located in more than 70 countries.")
                .homepage-spacer-lg

                = link_to [:map, :labs], class: 'box-link' do
                    = t("views.alt.lab_card.cta", default: "See the Fablabs Map")
                    = image_tag ("icons/arrow-right.svg")
        .col-xs-12.col-md-6
            .homepage-box
                =image_tag ("home/person-illustration.png"), :class => "homepage-box-image"
                .text-small
                    = t("views.alt.who_card.subtitle", default: "Who")
                .text-large
                    = t("views.alt.who_card.title", default: "Who is this platform for?")
                .text-medium
                    = t("views.alt.who_card.description", default: "This is a human based design platform mainly for fabbers but we welcome any maker, hacker, DIY and amateur in digital fabrication that wants to create, collaborate and share projects and knoledge")
                .homepage-spacer-lg

                = link_to signup_path, class: 'box-link' do
                    = t("views.home.lab_card.cta", default: "Join the community")
                    = image_tag ("icons/arrow-right.svg")
        .col-xs-12
            .container
                .homepage-quote.text-primary
                    .homepage-divider
                    = t("views.home.quote2", default: "Because all Fab Labs share common tools and processes, the program is building a global network, a distributed laboratories for research and invention.")
